singing doo dah a performance with stanford continuing studies events at stanford singing doo dah a performance with stanford continuing studies facebook twitter email print add to calendar please join marsha genensky one of the founding members of the internationally renowned vocal quartet anonymous 4 guitarist scott nygaard and singers from her spring quarter continuing studies course for a concert of songs by the earliest professional american songwriters they will perform songs like oh susanna my old kentucky home beautiful dreamer hard times come again no more lorena just before the battle mother and darling nelly gray written by stephen foster the first full time american songwriter george f root joseph webster and their contemporaries these songs became part of the american consciousness influenced songwriters of every generation that followed and are still popular today when tuesday june 12 2012 7 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where campbell recital hall braun music center map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags arts lecture reading music sponsor continuing studies contact 725 2650 continuingstudies stanford edu admission free and open to public permalink http events stanford edu events 310 31055 more info last modified february 10 2012
